node.text:
Now that the new year is here I feel it’s important to share this with you so can all be aware of the abuse that these beautiful animals go through so people can take some cute photos during their vacation. .
hope this Video🎥 can open Your eyes👀 a bit and give you a perspective on "Animal Interaction“ you might never had before!🤷🏼‍♂️ It‘s all up to US (Humans) if we accept things like this or not! If we support these things or not! 😓
•
Please SHARE this Video and help us shine a light on this serious global🌍 problem‼️Together we CAN END Animal Cruelty & Slavery🐾⛓
•
Also tag at least 3 Friends in the comments so we can spread this message. .
.
Thank you @dean.schneider for all the work you’re doing!

node.text:
Known as the most prominent geological fault in the Alpstein region, Saxer Lücke forms a gap in the ridgeline and is one of the greatest hikes in the area. 
🎥 @evyinswitzerland
📍 Saxer Lücke, Switzerland
🎶 Scars To Your Beautiful - Alessia Cara

node.text:
@joshmcca shares a Must-do Banff itinerary - I get asked this daily so I thought I’d create a post to help more people out. 
⁣
Favourite hikes 🥾- Big Beehive (tea house on trail), Plain of Six Glaciers (tea house), Mount Fairview, Sentinel Pass, Consolation Lakes, Eiffel Peak (long, scramble), EEOR (scramble), Devils Thumb (scramble), Tower of Babel (scramble), Mount Temple (hard, long, scramble), Tunnel Mountain (short, easy). ⁣
⁣
Don’t want to hike? Take the Banff Gondola up Sulphur Mountain. 🚠⁣
⁣
Cruise the Icefield Parkway 🚗 - This stretch of highway connects Banff National Park and Jasper National Park and is said to be one of the most scenic drives in the world. Lots of stops and wildlife to see along the way. (Video is from this highway). ⁣Please drive carefully and respect the wildlife’s space.
⁣
Favourite lakes 💦 Moraine Lake, Lake Louise, Herbert Lake (has a diving board), Peyto Lake, Bow Lake, Waterfowl lakes, Emerald Lake, Rundle Forebay. ⁣
⁣
Favourite spots to eat 🥘- The Grizzly House Banff, The Grizzly Paw Brewing 🍻, Park Distillery, Farm and Fire. ⁣
⁣
Where to camp 🏕 Two Jack Lake (One of my favourites), Waterfowl Lakes, Mosquito, Silverhorn. If those are all full Tunnel Mountain Village 1 usually has a spot + cell service for a backup. ⁣
⁣

node.text:
A rare male albino peacock showing his beautiful feathers. Albino peacocks are quite rare and it's unclear if the bird is actually an albino. White peafowls are born with a condition known as leucism, which reduces various pigments in their body. Though leucism can cause animals to be quite tame in some different species, this is not the case with the white peacock. They're just as feisty as their colorful counterparts and tend to peck and kick those who try to handle them. Still, it's impossible not to be dazzled by their appearance. 

🎥  @beeutifullviews
